### System file to start minecraft on boot
###   edit the path to match your system
###   edit the user to match who you want to launch your server as
### To create the symlink do the following as root:
#    # cp /<path>/minecraft-scripts/minecraft /etc/init.d
#    # cd /etc/rc5.d
#    # ln -s ../init.d/minecraft S01minecraft
#

su -c '/<path>/minecraft-scripts/all-start.sh' <user>
